cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on clusters and their power consumption in the context of scale-out workloads. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the utilization of different workloads and the potential of power and resource provisioning techniques to improve energy proportionality. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the component-level power distribution on a cluster and evaluates the potential of power provisioning techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the trade-offs between power and latency in active low-power modes. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a less likely category, but still relevant as the paper evaluates the power consumption of different workloads and the potential of power and resource provisioning techniques to improve energy proportionality.
